        "Cardiovascular effects: Decrease in BP is dose dependent due to peripheral vasodilation; cardiac output is maintained. Use caution in patients who are hypovolemic, hypotensive, or ..." to "Cardiovascular effects: Decrease in BP is dose dependent due to peripheral vasodilation; cardiac output is maintained. Use caution in patients who are hypovolemic, hypotensive, or ...",
        "Cardiovascular effects: IV use of рhеոуlерhrine may cause severe bradycardia (likely baroreflex mediated) and reduced cardiac output due to an increase in cardiac afterload especia..." to "Cardiovascular effects: IV use of phenylephrine may cause severe bradycardia (likely baroreflex mediated) and reduced cardiac output due to an increase in cardiac afterload especia...",
        "Carefully examine each prefilled syringe or vial to ensure the correct concentration is selected. Dosing: For weight-based IV heрariո, an institution-specific dosing nomogram may help to achieve therapeutic anticoagulation more rapidly (see example based on aPTT under \\\"Venous thromboembolism t..." to "Carefully examine each prefilled syringe or vial to ensure the correct concentration is selected. Dosing: For weight-based IV heparin, an institution-specific dosing nomogram may help to achieve therapeutic anticoagulation more rapidly (see example based on aPTT under \\\"Venous thromboembolism t...",
        "Ceftriakson ile birlikte verme (Ca-ceftriakson çökeltisi; neonatlarda fatal akciğer/böbrek hasarı)." to "Do not coadminister with ceftriaxone (Ca-ceftriaxone precipitate; fatal lung/kidney damage in neonates).",
        "Cerrahi 4 saati aşarsa veya masif kanama (>1500 mL) varsa intraoperatif doz tekrarlanmalıdır." to "If surgery exceeds 4 hours or there is massive bleeding (>1500 mL), the intraoperative dose should be repeated.",
        "Cerrahi 6 saati aşarsa intraoperatif doz tekrarlanmalıdır." to "If surgery exceeds 6 hours, the intraoperative dose should be repeated.",
        "Cerrahi Basıyı Sorgulayın: Cerrahın vena kava inferior basısı yapıp yapmadığını kontrol edin, masayı sola eğin veya cerraha basıyı gevşettirin." to "Question Surgical Compression: Check whether the surgeon is applying inferior vena cava compression, tilt the table to the left or have the surgeon relieve the pressure.",
        "Cerrahi Erteleme Gerekmez: Ameliyata devam edilebilir. Hastanın kronik antihipertansif ilaçlarını (Beta-blokerler, Kalsiyum kanal blokerleri) ameliyat sabahı az suyla almasını sağlayın. ACE inhibitörleri/ARB'leri vazopleji riskini önlemek için genellikle 24 saat önce kesilmelidir." to "No Surgical Postponement Required: Surgery can proceed. Ensure the patient takes their chronic antihypertensive medications (beta-blockers, calcium channel blockers) on the morning of surgery with a small amount of water. ACE inhibitors/ARBs should generally be discontinued 24 hours prior to prevent the risk of vasoplegia.",
        "Cerrahi Uyarılara Ara Verin: Vagal uyarılara yol açan cerrahi manipülasyonu (çekme, germe, göz kası basısı) derhal durdurtun. Laparoskopide karın gazını boşalttırın." to "Discontinue Surgical Stimulations: Immediately discontinue any surgical manipulation that causes vagal stimulation (pulling, stretching, eye muscle compression). Have the abdominal gas removed during laparoscopy.",
        "Cerrahi anestezi için %0.75, analjezi için %0.2 tercih edilir." to "0.75% is preferred for surgical anesthesia, and 0.2% for analgesia.",
        "Cerrahi bitti, hasta ekstübe edilmek isteniyor. Objektif nöromüsküler monitörde (TOF-Watch/TOFscan) ölçülen TOF oranı nedir?" to "Surgery is complete; the patient is ready for extubation. What is the TOF ratio measured by the objective neuromuscular monitor (TOF-Watch/TOFscan)?",
        "Cerrahi havayolu ihtiyacı doğduğunda KBB veya Genel Cerrahi desteğini acil çağırmak" to "Urgently call ENT or General Surgery support when a surgical airway is needed",
