        "Dantrolen dozu, flakon sayısı ve kriz protokol adımları" to "Dantrolene dosage, number of vials and crisis protocol steps",
        "Dantrolen dozunu kriz çözülene kadar 10 mg/kg'a kadar tekrarlayabilmek" to "Ability to repeat the dantrolene dose up to 10 mg/kg until the crisis is resolved.",
        "Dantrolene Sodium" to "Dantrolene Sodium",
        "Dar Açılı Glokom Atağı" to "Narrow Angle Glaucoma Attack",
        "Dar QRS (SVT/Sinüs Taşikardisi vb.) Yönetimi: \n1. Sinüs taşikardisi ise altta yatan nedenleri (ağrı, yetersiz anestezi derinliği, hipovolemi) tedavi edin. \n2. SVT şüphesi varsa Vagal Manevralar (karotis masajı) uygulayın. \n3. Düzelmezse Adenozin 6 mg IV hızlı bolus uygulayın. Başarısız olursa 12 mg tekrarlayın." to "Narrow QRS (SVT/Sinus Tachycardia etc.) Management: \n1. If sinus tachycardia, treat the underlying causes (pain, inadequate depth of anesthesia, hypovolemia). \n2. If SVT is suspected, perform Vagal Maneuvers (carotid massage). \n3. If not improved, administer Adenosine 6 mg IV rapid bolus. If unsuccessful repeat 12 mg.",
        "Dar QRS (SVT/Sinüs Taşikardisi vb.) Yönetimi: \\n1. Sinüs taşikardisi ise altta yatan nedenleri (ağrı, yetersiz anestezi derinliği, hipovolemi) tedavi edin. \\n2. SVT şüphesi varsa Vagal Manevralar (karotis masajı) uygulayın. \\n3. Düzelmezse Adenozin 6 mg IV hızlı bolus uygulayın. Başarısız olursa 12 mg tekrarlayın." to "Narrow QRS (SVT/Sinus Tachycardia etc.) Management: \\n1. If sinus tachycardia, treat underlying causes (pain, inadequate depth of anesthesia, hypovolemia). \\n2. If SVT is suspected, perform Vagal Maneuvers (carotid massage). \\n3. If unsuccessful, administer Adenosine 6 mg IV rapid bolus. If unsuccessful, repeat 12 mg.",
        "Dar QRS Sinüs Taşikardisi: Nedenini (ağrı, yetersiz anestezi, hipovolemi) bularak tedavi edin. Gerekirse Esmolol uygulayın." to "Narrow QRS Sinus Tachycardia: Find and treat the cause (pain, inadequate anesthesia, hypovolemia). Apply Esmolol if necessary.",
        "Dar QRS Stabil Düzenli SVT: Vagal manevralar (karotis masajı) deneyin. Yanıt alınamazsa **Adenozin 6 mg IV** hızlı bolus (büyük damardan) uygulayın. Gerekirse dozu 12 mg'a yükseltin." to "Narrow QRS Stable Regular SVT: Try vagal maneuvers (carotid massage). If no response, administer **Adenosine 6 mg IV** rapid bolus (intravenously). Increase dose to 12 mg if necessary.",
        "Dar QRS Supraventriküler Taşikardi (SVT) veya Sinüs Taşikardisi" to "Narrow QRS Supraventricular Tachycardia (SVT) or Sinus Tachycardia",
        "Dar QRS stabil SVT: Vagal manevralar uygulayın, yetmezse Adenozin 6 mg IV hızlı bolus yapın." to "Narrow QRS stable SVT: Apply vagal maneuvers, if not sufficient, administer Adenosine 6 mg IV rapid bolus.",
        "Dar açılı glokom" to "narrow angle glaucoma",
        "Dar açılı glokomda dikkat (akut glokom)" to "Caution in narrow-angle glaucoma (acute glaucoma)",
        "Dar açılı glokomda dikkat; göz içi basıncını artırabilir." to "Caution in narrow-angle glaucoma; may increase intraocular pressure.",
        "Dağılım yarı ömrü 2-4 dk, terminal yarı ömrü 24 saat" to "Distribution half-life 2-4 min, terminal half-life 24 hours",
        "Decreased blood flow: May cause decrease in hepatic and/or renal blood flow...." to "Decreased blood flow: May cause decrease in hepatic and/or renal blood flow....",
        "Defibrilatör ritminde ROSC (spontan dolaşımın dönmesi) sağlandığında ETCO₂'nin aniden 35-40 mmHg üzerine fırlaması" to "ETCO₂ suddenly rises above 35-40 mmHg when ROSC (return of spontaneous circulation) is achieved in defibrillator rhythm",
        "Dekompanse Kalp Yetmezliği, ciddi semptomatik Aort Darlığı elektif cerrahi için mutlak erteleme nedenidir." to "Decompensated Heart Failure and severe symptomatic Aortic Stenosis are absolute reasons for postponement of elective surgery.",
        "Dekompanse kalp yetmezliğinde kontrendike; bronkospastik hastalıkta dikkatle" to "Contraindicated in decompensated heart failure; use cautiously in bronchospastic disease",
        "Deksametazon mineralokortikoid aktivite sağlamaz; kronik primer adrenal yetmezlik/krizde hidrokortizon tercih edilir." to "Dexamethasone provides no mineralocorticoid activity; hydrocortisone preferred for chronic primary adrenal insufficiency/crisis.",
        "Deksametazona karşı bilinen aşırı duyarlılık" to "Known hypersensitivity to dexamethasone",
        "Dekstroz (Glukoz)" to "Dekstroz (Glukoz)",
        "Dengeli ampirik MTP paketlerine (1:1:1 oranında) devam edin. Her 4-6 ünitede bir iyonize kalsiyum kontrolü yapın ve 1 ampul Kalsiyum Klorür ekleyin. Asidoz ve hipotermiyi aktif olarak engelleyin." to "Continue balanced empirical MTP packs (1:1:1 ratio). Check ionized calcium every 4-6 units and add 1 ampoule Calcium Chloride. Actively prevent acidosis and hypothermia.",
        "Dengeli anestezide (%25 iyileşmeye kadar) 25-40 dakika; %95 iyileşme ~45-65 dakika; hipotermi uzatabilir" to "Under balanced anesthesia (to 25% recovery) 25-40 minutes; 95% recovery ~45-65 minutes; hypothermia may prolong",
        "Dental anesthesia Dental anesthesia: Infiltration or conduction block: Children &lt;10 years: Doses &gt;40 mg (1 mL) as ..." to "Dental anesthesia Dental anesthesia: Infiltration or conduction block: Children &lt;10 years: Doses &gt;40 mg (1 mL) as ...",
        "Dental anesthesia Dental anesthesia: Infiltration or conduction block: Children &lt;10 years: Doses &gt;40 mg (1 mL) as a 4% solution per procedure rarely needed for procedures involving a single tooth, in a maxillary infiltration for 2 to 3 teeth, or for an entire quadrant with a mandibular block. Children ≥10 years and Adolescents: Refer to adult dosing. Dosage adjustment for concomitant therapy..." to "Dental anesthesia Dental anesthesia: Infiltration or conduction block: Children &lt;10 years: Doses &gt;40 mg (1 mL) as a 4% solution per procedure rarely needed for procedures involving a single tooth, in a maxillary infiltration for 2 to 3 teeth, or for an entire quadrant with a mandibular block. Children ≥10 years and Adolescents: Refer to adult dosing. Dosage adjustment for concomitant therapy...",
        "Dental anesthesia Dental anesthesia: Infiltration or conduction block: Initial: 40 to 80 mg (1 to 2 mL) as a 4% solution." to "Dental anesthesia Dental anesthesia: Infiltration or conduction block: Initial: 40 to 80 mg (1 to 2 mL) as a 4% solution.",
        "Depolarizan nöromüsküler blokör (Asetilkolin Agonisti)" to "Depolarizing neuromuscular blocker (Acetylcholine Agonist)",
        "Depolarizan olmayan nöromüsküler blokör (Asetilkolin Antagonisti)" to "Non-depolarizing neuromuscular blocker (Acetylcholine Antagonist)",
        "Depolarizan olmayan nöromüsküler blokör (Benzilizokinolin grubu)" to "Non-depolarizing neuromuscular blocker (Benzylisoquinoline group)",
